This paper deals with the analysis of Markov chains on graphs, specifically Glauber dynamics for colorings. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as well as computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also uses techniques from graph theory (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) to prove its results. Additionally, the paper discusses the application of its results to list coloring, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
